{"lemma":"عَكِر","slug":"عَكِر","root":"ع.ك.ر","root_slug":"ع-ك-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ك-ر","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30060","","n30063","n30064","n30065"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%90%D8%B1"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be muddy, to be disturbed"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to put into disorder, to make turbid, to irritate, to unsettle"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَكِرَ (ʕakira) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"muddiness, darkness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dregs, settlings"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"murky, muddy"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to turn back, to incline, to return"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to backlash"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"origin, genesis, original state, custom, habit"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ع ك ر (ʕ k r), related to muddiness.\n\nFrom the root ع ك ر (ʕ k r), related to turning back."},"ipa":["/ʕa.ki.ra/","/ʕak.ka.ra/","/ʕa.kar/","/ʕa.kir/","/ʕa.ka.ra/","/ʕikr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30060","headword_ar":"عَكَرَ","root":"Ekr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EakorN","text_ar":"عَكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EukuwrN","text_ar":"عُكُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEokarN","text_ar":"مَعْكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in the Ham p. 200],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inclined;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turned back; returned:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnEkr","text_ar":"انعكر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[likewise] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, turned"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inclined;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became turned"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inclined."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eakara bihi baEiyruhu","text_ar":"عَكَرَ بِهِ بَعِيرُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His camel turned with him towards his family, and overcame him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajara bihi","text_ar":"عَجَرَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; (S, O;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overcame him, and turned back."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eakara","text_ar":"عَكَرَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"عَلَى الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EakorN","text_ar":"عَكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EukuwrN","text_ar":"عُكُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEtkr","text_ar":"اعتكر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He turned back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returned, against the thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"far~a mino qironihi vum~a Eakara Ealayohi biAlr~umoHi","text_ar":"فَرَّ مِنْ قِرْنِهِ ثُمَّ عَكَرَ عَلَيْهِ بِالرُّمْحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fled from his adversary,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wheeled about widely from him, then"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turned back against him with the spear:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEtkr","text_ar":"اعتكر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[likewise] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he turned back"},{"kind":"text","text":"[against his adversary]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after fleeing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wheeling about widely"},{"kind":"text","text":"[from him]. (IDrd, O.) [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eakara Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَكَرَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a saying)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contradicted it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, another saying;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was contradictory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repugnant, to it."},{"kind":"text","text":"See an"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2120},{"kind":"text","text":"ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboEN","text_ar":"سَبْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-  [And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He returned to the thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"See an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaradN","text_ar":"قَرَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] You say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eakara Alz~amaAnu","text_ar":"عَكَرَ الزَّمَانُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi bixayorK","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ بِخَيْرٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fortune turned towards him with good."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKtt.)       -A2-  [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eakara","text_ar":"عَكَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also trans. as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made"},{"kind":"text","text":"his soul"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to turn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., against another in fight: see Ham p. 200.]       -A3-  See also 4.       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eakira","text_ar":"عَكِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EakarN","text_ar":"عَكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(water, S, O, K, and wine, S, O, and beverage of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabiy*","text_ar":"نَبِيذ"},{"kind":"text","text":", K, and oil, S, O)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became dreggy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feculent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turbid."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eakirati Almisorajapu","text_ar":"عَكِرَتِ المِسْرَجَةُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lamp had dregs collected in it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","Mgh","A","TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n30063","headword_ar":"عِكْرٌ","root":"Ekr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSolN","text_ar":"اَصْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Origin;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"original state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"natural disposition"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, O, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EitorN","text_ar":"عِتْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa kariymu AlEikori","text_ar":"هُوَ كَرِيمُ العِكْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is of generous origin."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAEa fulaAnN Eikorahu","text_ar":"بَاعَ فُلَانٌ عِكْرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDihi","text_ar":"اَرْضِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eikorapa","text_ar":"عِكْرَةَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one sold the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSol","text_ar":"اَصْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fundamental property,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the property itself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of his land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa fulaAnN A_ilaY Eikorihi","text_ar":"رَجَعَ فُلَانٌ اـِلَى عِكْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one returned to his original state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"natural disposition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EitorN","text_ar":"عِتْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Custom; habit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAdato liEikorihaA lamiysu","text_ar":"عَادَتْ لِعِكْرِهَا لَمِيسُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lemees"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a proper name of a woman]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returned to her custom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"habit."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, L.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EitorN","text_ar":"عِتْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] And it is said in a trad., that when the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aiqotaraba","text_ar":"اِقْتَرَبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liln~aAsi HisaAbuhumo","text_ar":"لِلنَّاسِ حِسَابُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the Kur xxi. 1] were revealed, those who were in error refrained a little from what was forbidden, and then"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAduwA A_ilaY Eikorihimo","text_ar":"عَادُوا اـِلَى عِكْرِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they returned to their original bad way of acting"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of opinion, and to their evil deeds:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA:) or, accord. to one relation of the trad., ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlY Eakarihimo","text_ar":"الى عَكَرِهِمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to their filthiness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EakarN","text_ar":"عَكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"relating to oil: (O, TA:) but the former is the more proper. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n30064","headword_ar":"عَكَرٌ","root":"Ekr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dregs, feces, lees,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sediment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what remains at the bottom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, K,) of oil, (S, Mgh, O,) &c., (S, O,) and of the beverage called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabiy*","text_ar":"نَبِيذ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) or of anything; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is thick, and subsides,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of oil and the like; (Msb;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"last and thick part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of water and of wine and of oil: (S, O:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dust;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trbp","text_ar":"تربة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IKtt [but see 4].) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rust"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a sword (IAar, S, O, K) &c. (IAar, S.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EikorN","text_ar":"عِكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","O","K","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n30065","headword_ar":"عَكِرٌ","root":"Ekr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dreggy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feculent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"wine [&c.]. (S, O.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}